1
00:00:01,802 --> 00:00:04,069
-<i> PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.  
- MAMA!                         


2
00:00:04,137 --> 00:00:06,238
- THEY'RE TRYING TO HURT HER!   
- MAMA, NO!                     


3
00:00:06,307 --> 00:00:09,007
    -<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>               
    - BRING JAROD BACK.         


4
00:00:09,076 --> 00:00:13,378
- MY FATHER WANTS ME TO DO IT.  
- I'M NOT AFRAID OF YOUR FATHER.


5
00:00:13,447 --> 00:00:17,549
    <i> I HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE</i>   
    <i> MY MOTHER MAY HAVE RESCUED</i> 
    <i> THESE CHILDREN.</i>            


6
00:00:19,086 --> 00:00:21,153
        [ Fly Buzzing ]         


7
00:00:21,222 --> 00:00:24,656
YOU KNOW, GATOR HEAVEN HAS      
THE FINEST GATOR WRESTLING...   


8
00:00:24,724 --> 00:00:26,758
<i>IN ALL OF SOUTH FLORIDA.</i>        


9
00:00:26,827 --> 00:00:31,763
<i>IN FACT, WE PRODUCE</i>             
<i>MORE WRESTLING CHAMPIONS THAN</i>   
<i>ANY OTHER ROADSIDE ATTRACTION.</i>  


10
00:00:35,402 --> 00:00:39,170
- THAT'S JAROD?                 
- CAN YOU BELIEVE HE MASTERED   
  GATOR WRESTLING IN A WEEK?    


11
00:00:39,239 --> 00:00:42,774
        A REGULAR TARZAN.       
<i>GAVE 'EM ALL NICKNAMES TOO.</i>     


12
00:00:42,842 --> 00:00:46,011
CALLED THE ONE WITH THE SHARPEST
TEETH MISS PARKER.              


13
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:48,513
BEEN GONE ABOUT A MONTH.        


14
00:00:48,582 --> 00:00:51,215
DID HE LEAVE ANYTHING BEHIND?   
LIKE A RED NOTEBOOK?            


15
00:00:51,284 --> 00:00:53,852
HE LEFT SOMETHIN' BETTER.       


16
00:00:53,921 --> 00:00:56,587
SAID THIS WAS FOR YOU.          
                BEAUTIFUL.      


17
00:00:56,656 --> 00:01:00,392
GENUINE NATIVE ART.             
HANDCRAFTED BY THE TRIBE.       


18
00:01:00,461 --> 00:01:02,527
                IN TAIWAN?      


19
00:01:02,596 --> 00:01:05,464
EASTERN TRIBE.                  


20
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:11,102
    LOVELY, JAROD.              
    ANOTHER GAME.               


21
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:14,039
SAID IF YOU WANTED IT,          
YOU HAD TO SIGN FOR IT.         


22
00:01:18,678 --> 00:01:20,478
                    THANK YOU.  


23
00:01:20,547 --> 00:01:24,115
NO. JAROD SAID THE PEN          
WAS FOR YOU TOO.                


24
00:01:54,715 --> 00:01:57,148
    [ Sighs ]                   


25
00:02:11,398 --> 00:02:13,631
                <i> [ Man ]</i>        
                <i> THERE IT IS.</i>   


26
00:02:17,404 --> 00:02:21,039
NOW COME ON, BUBBA.             
WE GOTTA RELOCATE               
THIS PREHISTORIC HANDBAG...     


27
00:02:21,107 --> 00:02:22,874
<i>BEFORE THE HURRICANE EVAC.</i>      


28
00:02:26,213 --> 00:02:29,214
REPORTS GOT IT COMIN' IN        
PRETTY FAST TOO.                
    IT'S STILL A FEW HOURS OFF. 


29
00:02:29,282 --> 00:02:32,784
    <i> IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE A DAY</i> 
    <i> THIS BEAUTIFUL IS GONNA</i>    
    <i> TURN INTO A STORM.</i>         


30
00:02:32,852 --> 00:02:35,387
    WELL, IF YOU'RE IN A HURRY, 
    I COULD WRESTLE IT FOR YOU. 


31
00:02:35,456 --> 00:02:36,988
WHAT? THE GATOR?                
                    YEAH.       


32
00:02:37,057 --> 00:02:40,892
YOU LOST YOUR MIND, BUBBA.      
            I USED TO WRESTLE   
            FOR THE SEMINOLES.  


33
00:02:40,961 --> 00:02:43,528
FLORIDA STATE?                  
                NO. THE TRIBE.  


34
00:02:43,597 --> 00:02:46,365
                COME HERE, GIRL.
WHOA, WHOA. WAIT A MINUTE.      


35
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:48,499
HOW DO YOU KNOW                 
THAT'S A SHE?                   


36
00:02:50,471 --> 00:02:52,204
            I KNOW THAT SMILE.  


37
00:02:52,273 --> 00:02:55,774
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


38
00:03:51,965 --> 00:03:54,633
    MISS PARKER,                
    YOU'RE TO COME WITH ME.     


39
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,774
    DADDY, THE NEXT TIME        
    THAT YOU WANT TO SEE ME,    


40
00:04:02,843 --> 00:04:06,678
    YOU DON'T HAVE TO SEND      
    THE WELCOME WAGON.          


41
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:12,216
<i>YOU'RE HERE AT MY INVITATION,</i>   
<i>NOT YOUR FATHER'S.</i>              


42
00:04:12,285 --> 00:04:15,353
            <i> YOU'VE BEEN BUSY.</i>  


43
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:17,355
I DON'T FOLLOW YOU, SIR.        


44
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:21,092
                I FOLLOW YOU.   


45
00:04:25,532 --> 00:04:29,568
        <i> WHAT WAS IN</i>            
        <i> THE SAFETY DEPOSIT BOX?</i>


46
00:04:31,071 --> 00:04:33,005
    NOTHING, SIR.               


47
00:04:33,073 --> 00:04:36,107
        LET ME REPHRASE,        
        MISS PARKER.            


48
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:40,312
    I KNOW IT WAS MOMMY'S BOX.  


49
00:04:40,381 --> 00:04:45,149
    <i> WHAT DID YOU FIND IN IT?</i>   
    <i> [ Wheezing ]</i>               


50
00:04:45,218 --> 00:04:47,885
I WAS LOOKING FOR ANSWERS.      


51
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,988
            ABOUT WHAT?         


52
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:52,523
    ABOUT HOW SHE DIED.         


53
00:04:52,592 --> 00:04:57,095
    -<i> YOUR MOTHER SHOT HERSELF.</i> 
    - DADDY.                    


54
00:04:58,932 --> 00:05:01,666
        LEAVE US, MR. RAINES.   


55
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:07,338
            DON'T I GET A HUG?  


56
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:14,412
    [ Laughs ]                  
    BEEN TOO LONG.              


57
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:17,415
SO, HOW ARE THINGS              
AT THE SUMMER HOUSE?            


58
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,484
ARE THE LEAVES COMING BACK?     


59
00:05:19,553 --> 00:05:22,520
        SLOWLY. YOU KNOW HOW    
        SPRING CAN BE UP THERE. 


60
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:26,391
STUBBORN. YOUR MOTHER           
ALWAYS GOT IMPATIENT.           


61
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:29,761
            I DON'T REMEMBER    
            THAT ABOUT HER.     


62
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:34,532
            BUT I--             
            I DO REMEMBER THIS. 


63
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:51,916
    YOU LOOK LIKE HER.          
    WATCHING YOU,               


64
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:54,719
IN SOME WAYS                    
SHE NEVER LEFT.                 


65
00:05:54,788 --> 00:05:59,157
    DADDY, I WANT TO KNOW       
    WHAT HAPPENED TO MY MOTHER. 


66
00:05:59,225 --> 00:06:02,961
- I'M DISAPPOINTED IN YOU.      
-<i> YOU'RE</i> DISAPPOINTED IN<i> ME?</i>    


67
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,929
DON'T TELL ME                   
YOU BELIEVE THIS CRAP.          


68
00:06:04,998 --> 00:06:08,566
        BUT I REMEMBER          
        THAT THANKSGIVING!      
        THE FIGHT THAT YOU HAD. 


69
00:06:08,635 --> 00:06:11,169
        AND A FEW MONTHS LATER, 
        SHE WAS DEAD.           


70
00:06:11,237 --> 00:06:13,304
DON'T LET YOUR EMOTIONS         
RUN AWAY WITH YOU.              


71
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,440
I TAUGHT YOU BETTER.            


72
00:06:15,509 --> 00:06:19,277
    JUST TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED. 


73
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:23,848
    I KILLED HER.               


74
00:06:23,917 --> 00:06:27,752
AT LEAST, THAT'S WHAT           
I TORTURE MYSELF BELIEVING.     


75
00:06:29,122 --> 00:06:32,190
WHEN SOMEONE YOU LOVE           
COMMITS SUICIDE,                


76
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:35,460
YOU SEARCH FOR ANSWERS          
TO THE MYSTERY                  
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.           


77
00:06:35,528 --> 00:06:38,062
THAT'S WHAT                     
YOU'RE DOING NOW.               


78
00:06:46,606 --> 00:06:48,606
                I MISS HER.     


79
00:06:48,675 --> 00:06:53,178
YOU WERE YOUNG. THERE'S NO WAY  
YOU COULD'VE KNOWN              
WHAT SHE WAS GOING THROUGH.     


80
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:57,715
<i>IT WAS A SAD TIME.</i>              
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHY SHE LEFT US.</i>   


81
00:06:59,153 --> 00:07:01,820
DON'T YOU THINK                 
I MISS HER TOO?                 


82
00:07:03,723 --> 00:07:05,856
                OF COURSE.      


83
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:09,393
YOU CAN BELIEVE YOUR FATHER     
OR JAROD. WHO'S IT GOING TO BE? 


84
00:07:12,398 --> 00:07:16,001
            DADDY, I WANT       
            A NEW ASSIGNMENT.   


85
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:19,070
        JAROD IS SYDNEY'S MESS, 
        AND MR. RAINES'S.       


86
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:21,372
        PLEASE PUT ME           
        BACK IN CORPORATE.      


87
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:24,809
WE HAVE OUR ARRANGEMENT.        
                I KNOW.         


88
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,615
YOU WERE A QUIET,               
UNCERTAIN LITTLE GIRL,          


89
00:07:30,684 --> 00:07:33,518
AND NOW YOU'RE THIS...          


90
00:07:33,587 --> 00:07:36,020
PRESENCE.                       


91
00:07:36,089 --> 00:07:39,591
IT'S TIME                       
FOR MY TREASURE TO SHINE!       


92
00:07:39,659 --> 00:07:42,927
I KNOW WHAT                     
YOU'RE CAPABLE OF.              


93
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:46,397
                DO YOU?         


94
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,867
        I DO.                   


95
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:51,703
    AND OUR DEAL STANDS.        


96
00:08:47,794 --> 00:08:50,328
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>FLORIDA?</i>                        
<i>I WAS THERE YESTERDAY.</i>          


97
00:08:50,396 --> 00:08:52,630
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>I KNOW. YOU JUST</i>                
<i>WEREN'T SOUTH ENOUGH.</i>           


98
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:58,502
WHILE YOU WERE AWAY,            
BROOTS AND I REVISITED THE OLD  
NOTEBOOK FROM THE ATLANTA SITE, 


99
00:08:58,572 --> 00:09:00,838
AND WE FOUND SOME CLUES.        


100
00:09:00,907 --> 00:09:04,776
GLOBAL COORDINATES              
WRITTEN IN IT THAT LEAD US TO-- 


101
00:09:04,845 --> 00:09:08,780
HURRICANE CASSANDRA. TOP WIND   
SPEEDS OF 150 MILES PER HOUR.   


102
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:10,648
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>WHEN JAROD WAS IN ATLANTA,</i>      


103
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:14,118
<i>CASSANDRA WAS JUST</i>              
<i>A BADLY FORMED TROPICAL</i>         
<i>DEPRESSION.</i>                     


104
00:09:14,187 --> 00:09:16,921
<i>HE MUST HAVE PREDICTED</i>          
<i>ITS COURSE.</i>                     


105
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:19,824
    JAROD PUT HIMSELF           
    IN THE PATH OF A HURRICANE? 


106
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,994
SOMEONE FROM MARINE PATROL      
IN BAHIA GRANDE IS USING        
THE CENTRE'S ACCESS CODE...     


107
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,530
<i>TO HACK INTO DEFENSE DEPARTMENT</i> 
<i>WEATHER SATELLITES.</i>             


108
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:27,933
IT'S THE SAME ONE I'M USING.    


109
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:31,268
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>
TECH ROOM. BROOTS.              


110
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:34,205
UH-- [ Clears Throat ]          
NO. YES, SIR.                   


111
00:09:34,273 --> 00:09:38,443
UH, RIGHT HERE. HOLD ON.        
IT'S FOR YOU.                   


112
00:09:38,511 --> 00:09:40,445
        YES.                    


113
00:09:44,551 --> 00:09:46,484
            OF COURSE.          


114
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:50,021
                VERY CLEAR.     


115
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,023
WHO WAS THAT?                   
            IT WAS PERSONAL.    


116
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:55,126
            HOW FAST CAN WE     
            GET DOWN THERE?     
    UH, A COUPLE OF HOURS.      


117
00:09:55,195 --> 00:09:58,996
    BUT THEY'RE ALREADY         
    STARTING TO EVACUATE        
    PEOPLE FROM SOUTH FLORIDA.  


118
00:09:59,066 --> 00:10:00,998
        THEN I'LL GO WITH SAM.  


119
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:03,335
<i>MISS PARKER, IT ISN'T SAFE.</i>     


120
00:10:03,403 --> 00:10:06,971
    IF JAROD'S REALLY           
    ON THAT ISLAND, I HAVE HIM  
    RIGHT WHERE WE WANT HIM.    


121
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:17,548
    - WHO WAS ON THAT CALL?     
    - MR. RAINES.               


122
00:10:28,295 --> 00:10:31,228
<i>[ Helicopter Approaching ]</i>      


123
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:50,248
<i>[ TV Announcer ]</i>                
<i>RESIDENTS AND MERCHANTS</i>         
<i>OF BAHIA GRANDE...</i>              


124
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:54,452
<i>ARE FRANTICALLY BOARDING UP</i>     
<i>WINDOWS AND PACKING CARS</i>        
<i>THIS AFTERNOON.</i>                 


125
00:10:54,521 --> 00:10:58,222
<i>CASSANDRA IS EXPECTED</i>           
<i>IN FOUR TO FIVE HOURS,</i>          
<i>AROUND 7:00 P.M. THIS EVENING.</i>  


126
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:01,959
<i>ISLANDERS ARE BEING REMINDED--</i>  
            I'M GONNA BE OUT--  
            OUT FRONT.          


127
00:11:02,028 --> 00:11:05,963
    <i> BUT DON'T WORRY, SIMONE.</i>   
    <i> WE'LL GET YOU TO THE DOCTOR</i>
    <i> REAL SOON.</i>                 


128
00:11:20,647 --> 00:11:22,080
                HEY!            


129
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:26,317
    BATTENING DOWN THE HATCHES? 
<i>I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.</i>             


130
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:30,889
MY CRACKER BUTT IS GONNA        
SELL THIS PLACE AND MOVE        
TO OKLAHOMA AFTER THIS ONE.     


131
00:11:30,957 --> 00:11:32,890
        FOR WHAT? TORNADOES?    


132
00:11:32,959 --> 00:11:35,259
OKAY. CALIFORNIA.               
                EARTHQUAKES?    


133
00:11:35,328 --> 00:11:37,494
SOMEWHERE 'SIDES HERE.          


134
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:40,164
            HOW'S SHE DOING?    


135
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,901
FEVER'S NOT BREAKING.           


136
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,170
            [ Sighs ]           
            YOU BETTER HURRY UP.


137
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:51,742
    JAROD, ARE YOU SURE         
    YOU SHOULD'VE PULLED SIMONE 
    OUT OF THAT FACILITY?       


138
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:53,744
THEY WERE GOING TO SHIP HER     
BACK TO HAITI.                  


139
00:11:53,813 --> 00:11:57,748
    I CAN'T BELIEVE BARTLETT    
    WOULD DO THAT-- JUST LET    
    HER FOLKS DIE IN A STORM.   


140
00:11:57,818 --> 00:12:00,685
PEOPLE WILL DO ALL KINDS        
OF THINGS FOR MONEY.            


141
00:12:00,754 --> 00:12:02,953
I'LL SEE THAT HE GETS PAID.     


142
00:12:03,022 --> 00:12:06,324
    <i> JAROD, FORGET ABOUT HIM.</i>   


143
00:12:06,393 --> 00:12:10,094
        COME GO WITH US. I, UH--


144
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:13,631
WHAT IS IT?                     
                I'M JUST--      


145
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:16,701
            I'M NOT VERY GOOD   
            AROUND SICK PEOPLE. 


146
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:19,704
            I WATCHED MY OLD MAN
            HAVE A HEART ATTACK.


147
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:23,207
            I KNEW HE NEEDED    
            C.P.R. OR SOMETHING,
            BUT I FROZE.        


148
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:26,710
        I JUST--                
         I WATCHED HIM GO.      


149
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:30,348
        I CAN'T HANDLE          
        THE RESPONSIBILITY.     


150
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:32,884
THE ANALGESIC I GAVE HER        
SHOULD HELP WITH HER FEVER.     


151
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:34,953
ALL YOU NEED TO DO              
IS DRIVE HER TO MIAMI.          


152
00:12:35,021 --> 00:12:37,388
THE DOCTORS                     
WILL TAKE OVER FROM THERE.      


153
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:40,891
YOU CAN DO IT.                  
I TRUST YOU.                    


154
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:46,330
            [ Sighs ]           
            IF YOU SAY SO.      


155
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:56,641
            -<i> JAROD.</i>            
            - HI.               


156
00:12:59,345 --> 00:13:02,914
        - IT'S EMPTY.           
        - NO MORE CANDY.        


157
00:13:02,982 --> 00:13:06,050
    DOCTOR'S ORDERS.            
    BUT I'LL GET YOU SOME MORE, 


158
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,720
        AS SOON AS WE SEE       
        YOUR FAMILY IN MIAMI.   


159
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,721
                I PROMISE.      


160
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:17,895
        [ Whispering ]          
        I'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.  


161
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:21,031
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>            


162
00:13:31,544 --> 00:13:33,711
        ARE YOU GONNA HELP ME   
        WITH THIS CAGE?         


163
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:37,849
<i>I CAN'T, SIR. I JUST GOT</i>        
<i>THIS DOWNLOAD FROM THE STATE</i>    
<i>DEPARTMENT OF LAW ENFORCEMENT.</i>  


164
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:41,953
<i>THEY SUSPECT THAT THE PARENTS</i>   
<i>OF THE HAITIAN GIRL WERE KILLED</i> 
<i>AROUND HARRISON MARSH.</i>          


165
00:13:42,021 --> 00:13:45,023
THEY WANT EVIDENCE GATHERED     
BEFORE CASSANDRA WASHES IT AWAY.


166
00:13:45,091 --> 00:13:47,024
        LET ME SEE THAT.        


167
00:13:51,097 --> 00:13:56,467
        HMM. UH, WHY DON'T YOU  
        FINISH UP HERE, AND I'LL
        TAKE CARE OF THIS.      


168
00:13:56,535 --> 00:13:59,803
    - I'LL GO WITH YOU.         
    - NO. I CAN HANDLE IT.      


169
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:25,929
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


170
00:14:25,998 --> 00:14:28,600
<i>[ Woman ] NO!</i>                   
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>I WON'T LET YOU DO IT!</i>          


171
00:14:28,668 --> 00:14:30,901
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>DON'T! YOU'RE HURTING ME!</i>       


172
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:33,004
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>COME BACK HERE!</i>                 


173
00:14:33,073 --> 00:14:35,906
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


174
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:46,017
        - [ Creaking ]          
        -<i> [ Thunderclap ]</i>       


175
00:14:54,627 --> 00:14:56,194
        FASTER, SAM.            


176
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:06,937
    OKAY. WE'RE GONNA BE LEAVING
    HERE IN JUST A FEW MINUTES. 


177
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:08,940
                OKAY?           


178
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:34,999
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


179
00:15:45,245 --> 00:15:47,912
            BOO!                


180
00:15:49,549 --> 00:15:52,316
            DAMN IT! YOU SCARED 
            THE HELL OUT OF ME. 


181
00:15:52,385 --> 00:15:56,721
            [ Shouts, Grunts ]  


182
00:15:56,790 --> 00:16:00,391
<i>I'M SORRY.</i>                      
            <i> HEY! HEY, BUBBA!</i>   


183
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:04,562
    WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?      
    ARE YOU GONNA STAND THERE   
    OR CUT ME OUT OF THIS?      


184
00:16:04,631 --> 00:16:07,899
CUT YOU OUT? I SPENT            
A LONG TIME MAKING THAT THING.  


185
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,368
            YOU RIGGED THIS NET?


186
00:16:10,437 --> 00:16:13,070
THINK OF IT AS A BAG.           


187
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:15,306
<i>A TRASH BAG.</i>                    


188
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:18,609
    YOU CUT ME OUT OF THIS NOW, 
    OR I'LL BLOW YOU AWAY!      


189
00:16:18,678 --> 00:16:22,112
MOST CRIMINALS, THEY SMUGGLE    
DRUGS OR STOLEN CARS.           


190
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:24,916
                DO IT!          
YOU TRADE IN HUMAN LIFE.        


191
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:29,020
YOU SMUGGLE HAITIANS,           
AND THEN YOU CHARGE             
THEIR FAMILIES IN MIAMI.        


192
00:16:29,088 --> 00:16:33,925
        [ Gun Clicks ]          
<i>AND ONCE YOU GET THEM HERE,</i>     
<i>YOU RAISE THE PRICE.</i>            


193
00:16:33,994 --> 00:16:37,528
    NOW THAT'S RANSOM,          
    PURE AND SIMPLE.            


194
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:41,298
AND IF THEY CAN'T AFFORD TO PAY,
WELL, YOU JUST LET 'EM DIE      
IN A STORM.                     


195
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:45,136
<i>KINDA LIKE THE ONE</i>              
<i>THAT'S COMING NOW.</i>              


196
00:16:45,205 --> 00:16:47,872
            YOU GOT NO PROOF    
            OF NOTHIN'!         


197
00:16:47,941 --> 00:16:50,775
I SENT IT TO THE STATE          
DEPARTMENT OF LAW ENFORCEMENT.  


198
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:55,479
<i>SIMONE'S FAMILY, THEY JUST</i>      
<i>WANTED TO START A NEW LIFE.</i>     


199
00:16:55,548 --> 00:16:58,282
BUT YOU TOOK THAT               
AWAY FROM THEM.                 


200
00:16:58,351 --> 00:17:01,752
AND THAT LITTLE GIRL, SHE       
DOESN'T HAVE A MOM AND DAD...   


201
00:17:01,821 --> 00:17:05,423
BECAUSE YOU LOCKED THEM OUT HERE
IN A SHACK TO DIE IN A STORM.   


202
00:17:05,492 --> 00:17:07,792
AS THE SHACK COLLAPSED          
AROUND THEM,                    


203
00:17:07,861 --> 00:17:10,327
<i>HER PARENTS THREW THEMSELVES</i>    
<i>ON THEIR DAUGHTER.</i>              


204
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:12,730
    THEY DIED TRYING            
    TO SAVE HER LIFE!           


205
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:19,002
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE      
TO GROW UP WITHOUT PARENTS?     


206
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:23,674
    HEY, HEY! BUBBA, WAIT, WAIT!


207
00:17:23,743 --> 00:17:26,677
    YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME OUT HERE!
    THIS HURRICANE'LL KILL ME!  


208
00:17:26,746 --> 00:17:29,146
OH, NO, IT WON'T.               


209
00:17:29,215 --> 00:17:32,983
YOU'RE ABOUT THREE MILES        
NORTH OF THE DAMAGE PATH.       


210
00:17:35,521 --> 00:17:38,022
AT LEAST I THINK SO...          


211
00:17:38,091 --> 00:17:41,759
    BUBBA.                      
                HEY! HEY!       


212
00:17:43,195 --> 00:17:47,965
        HEY! COME BACK HERE!    
        YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME HERE!


213
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:54,605
    YOU'RE DEAD! YOU'RE         
    DEAD, YOU SON OF A-- JAROD! 


214
00:17:54,674 --> 00:17:57,842
<i>[ Man On Radio ]</i>                
<i>THIS IS THE EMERGENCY</i>           
<i>BROADCAST SYSTEM.</i>               


215
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:01,912
<i>HURRICANE CASSANDRA IS MAKING</i>   
<i>LANDFALL AT THIS HOUR ALONG</i>     
<i>THE ISLAND'S EASTERN SHORE.</i>     


216
00:18:01,981 --> 00:18:04,382
<i>WINDS ARE AT 150 MILES PER HOUR.</i>


217
00:18:04,451 --> 00:18:06,984
<i>EVACUATION OF BAHIA GRANDE</i>      
<i>HAS BEEN COMPLETED.</i>             


218
00:18:07,052 --> 00:18:11,322
<i>REMAINING RESIDENTS ARE ADVISED</i> 
<i>TO SEEK SHELTER IN THE CENTER</i>   
<i>OF A SAFE, SECURE STRUCTURE.</i>    


219
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:19,930
        - I'M SORRY, JAROD.     
        - WHAT HAPPENED?        


220
00:18:19,999 --> 00:18:22,666
    <i> I GOT GOOD NEWS AND BAD.</i>   
    <i> BRIDGE IS WASHED AWAY.</i>     


221
00:18:22,736 --> 00:18:24,668
        POWER'S OUT.            
        PHONE LINES ARE DOWN.   


222
00:18:24,737 --> 00:18:27,371
<i>WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO RIDE OUT</i>    
<i>THE STORM HERE.</i>                 
        WHAT'S THE GOOD NEWS?   


223
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,241
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>THAT IS THE GOOD NEWS.</i>          


224
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:32,977
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>            


225
00:18:41,354 --> 00:18:43,287
PILOT HAD TO EVACUATE.          


226
00:18:43,356 --> 00:18:46,490
HE LOST CONTACT WITH MISS PARKER
20 MINUTES AGO.                 


227
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:49,427
<i>THANK YOU FOR MAKING US</i>         
<i>SOUTH FLORIDA'S CHOICE FOR NEWS.</i>


228
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:53,030
        FEED'S UP.              
<i>OUR TOP STORY IS--</i>              
<i>WHO ELSE-- CASSANDRA,</i>           


229
00:18:53,098 --> 00:18:58,368
WHOSE TOP WINDS HAVE NOW BEEN   
UPGRADED TO 175 MILES AN HOUR.  


230
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:00,938
CASSANDRA HAS VEERED            
30 DEGREES NORTH-NORTHEAST,     


231
00:19:01,006 --> 00:19:04,642
AND IT LOOKS LIKE BAHIA GRANDE  
WILL BEAR THE BRUNT             
OF CASSANDRA'S FURY.            


232
00:19:04,711 --> 00:19:07,644
WELL, CASSANDRA                 
HASN'T MET MISS PARKER.         


233
00:19:07,713 --> 00:19:11,949
<i>[ TV Continues, Indistinct ]</i>    
I HOPE THEY'RE ALL RIGHT.       


234
00:19:12,018 --> 00:19:13,851
    [ Cork Pops ]               


235
00:19:16,923 --> 00:19:21,191
    <i> AFTER ALL THOSE DEAD ENDS,</i> 
    <i> ALL I NEEDED WAS A LITTLE</i>  
    <i> HELP FROM CASSANDRA.</i>       


236
00:19:23,563 --> 00:19:26,397
        TO WOMEN.               
        HELL HATH NO FURY--     


237
00:19:26,465 --> 00:19:28,499
THAT ISN'T GOOD                 
FOR YOUR ULCER.                 


238
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:30,668
                NEITHER ARE YOU.


239
00:19:32,238 --> 00:19:35,172
DON'T UNDERESTIMATE             
THE POWER OF CASSANDRA.         


240
00:19:35,241 --> 00:19:39,510
HER WINDS ARE PROBABLY PEAKING  
AT 175 MILES PER HOUR.          


241
00:19:39,579 --> 00:19:43,014
    - THIS PLACE'LL HOLD.       
    - JUST IN CASE IT DOESN'T,  


242
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:47,851
        WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME   
        WHO MY PARENTS ARE?     


243
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,753
            TELL ME WHO I AM.   


244
00:19:53,425 --> 00:19:58,496
MAYBE I SHOULD SEND YOU         
TO EVERY Y.M.C.A.               
IN THE COUNTRY FIRST.           


245
00:19:58,564 --> 00:20:01,498
<i>OR LOCK YOU IN THE BATES MOTEL</i>  
<i>WITH SYDNEY AND BROOTS.</i>         


246
00:20:01,568 --> 00:20:04,835
THIS IS ABOUT THAT STRIP SEARCH 
IN LAS VEGAS, ISN'T IT?         


247
00:20:04,904 --> 00:20:09,740
        <i> COME ON. YOU'VE GOT ME.</i>
        <i> WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME?</i> 


248
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:17,114
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE WASTED YOUR  
TIME HELPING THE DOWNTRODDEN.   


249
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:21,018
                I HAVEN'T WASTED
                MY FREEDOM.     


250
00:20:21,087 --> 00:20:24,388
JAROD, YOU WERE                 
WRESTLING AN ALLIGATOR.         


251
00:20:24,457 --> 00:20:28,292
[ Laughing ]                    
            SO YOU GOT          
            THE MEDICAL REPORT. 


252
00:20:30,296 --> 00:20:33,063
I HAVE WHAT YOU FORGOT.         


253
00:20:33,132 --> 00:20:35,433
            YOU DIDN'T COME HERE
            JUST TO RETRIEVE ME.


254
00:20:35,502 --> 00:20:37,735
            <i> YOU WANT ANSWERS.</i>  


255
00:20:37,803 --> 00:20:40,570
I HAVE EVERYTHING I NEED.       


256
00:20:40,639 --> 00:20:43,207
DADDY'S GOING TO BE THRILLED.   


257
00:20:43,276 --> 00:20:46,277
    BUT DADDY DOESN'T GIVE YOU  
    WHAT YOU WANT NOW, DOES HE? 


258
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:51,115
        <i> WHAT DID DADDY TELL YOU</i>
        <i> ABOUT YOUR MOTHER'S...</i> 
        <i> SUICIDE?</i>               


259
00:20:51,184 --> 00:20:54,585
THAT'S ENOUGH!                  
    I BET IT WASN'T THE TRUTH.  


260
00:20:54,653 --> 00:20:57,722
YEAH, WELL, THE TRUTH IS        
YOU'RE A LIAR! ALWAYS HAVE BEEN.


261
00:20:57,790 --> 00:21:00,057
YOU FAKED THAT MEDICAL REPORT.  


262
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:01,993
        I WOULDN'T FAKE         
        SOMETHING LIKE THAT.    


263
00:21:02,061 --> 00:21:04,061
            I DIDN'T WANT       
            TO HAVE TO TELL YOU,


264
00:21:04,129 --> 00:21:07,064
        BUT I COULDN'T WITHHOLD 
        A KEY TO YOUR PAST.     


265
00:21:07,132 --> 00:21:09,700
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


266
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:12,703
[ Scoffs ]                      
NICE TRY.                       


267
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:18,809
YOU'RE SO IN CONTROL.           


268
00:21:18,878 --> 00:21:21,946
SO AHEAD OF THE GAME,           
AREN'T YOU?                     


269
00:21:22,014 --> 00:21:25,082
<i>WELL, NOT ANYMORE.</i>              
<i>NOW I MAKE THE RULES.</i>           


270
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:27,585
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


271
00:21:30,256 --> 00:21:34,592
        [ Grunting, Muttering ] 


272
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:55,246
<i> HOLD ON.</i>                       
<i> YOU'RE SUCH A GOOD, GOOD GIRL.</i> 


273
00:21:56,749 --> 00:21:59,816
HOW MANY MERIT BADGES           
DID<i> THIS</i> GET YOU?               


274
00:21:59,886 --> 00:22:03,019
        YOU DON'T THINK         
        THAT RESCUING CHILDREN  
        IS A GOOD IDEA?         


275
00:22:03,088 --> 00:22:05,623
        <i> YOUR MOTHER CERTAINLY</i>  
        <i> THOUGHT IT WAS.</i>        


276
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:08,326
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


277
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:12,396
            THE LEADING EDGE    
            JUST PASSED.        


278
00:22:12,465 --> 00:22:15,132
        <i> THE EYEWALL SHOULD HIT</i> 
        <i> IN ABOUT 17 MINUTES.</i>   


279
00:22:15,201 --> 00:22:17,401
<i>HONEY, WAKE UP.</i>                 
        THAT'S THE WORST PART.  


280
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:20,471
    - JAROD, I CAN'T WAKE HER.  
    - LET ME TAKE A LOOK AT HER.


281
00:22:20,539 --> 00:22:23,073
    - SAM CAN DO IT.            
    - SAM IS NOT A DOCTOR.      


282
00:22:23,142 --> 00:22:25,609
        I-- I CAN BE. PLEASE!   


283
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:28,045
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


284
00:22:32,318 --> 00:22:35,719
                SIMONE? IT'S ME.


285
00:22:35,788 --> 00:22:37,921
                    SIMONE.     


286
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:41,058
        <i> TALK TO ME. COME ON.</i>   


287
00:22:41,127 --> 00:22:44,095
                <i> SIMONE? SIMONE?</i>


288
00:22:44,163 --> 00:22:46,030
IF HE TRIES ANYTHING,           
SHOOT HIM IN THE FOOT.          


289
00:22:50,803 --> 00:22:54,071
            SIMONE? SIMONE,     
            CAN YOU HEAR ME?    


290
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:57,308
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


291
00:22:59,779 --> 00:23:01,879
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>NO!</i>                             
                <i> [ Man ]</i>        
                <i> LISTEN TO ME!</i>  


292
00:23:01,948 --> 00:23:03,881
<i>STOP!</i>                           
                <i> I KNOW WHAT</i>    
                <i> YOU'RE DOING!</i>  


293
00:23:03,950 --> 00:23:07,551
<i>YOU'RE HURTING ME!</i>              
    <i> WHERE ARE YOU GOING?</i>       
    <i> COME BACK HERE!</i>            


294
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:09,186
        [ Creaking ]            


295
00:23:13,426 --> 00:23:15,760
        SHE'S DIPPING IN AND OUT
        OF CONSCIOUSNESS.       


296
00:23:15,828 --> 00:23:18,362
                I NEED TO GET   
                HER FEVER DOWN. 


297
00:23:23,002 --> 00:23:27,037
    THE INFECTION IS SPREADING. 
    SHE NEEDS PENICILLIN.       


298
00:23:27,106 --> 00:23:29,940
        I CAN GET SOME          
        FROM THE FIRST AID KITS 
        AT THE BOATHOUSE.       


299
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:33,977
-<i> ACROSS THE ISLAND?</i>            
- AFTER THE STORM, WHILE YOU'RE 
  ON YOUR WAY TO BLUE COVE,     


300
00:23:34,046 --> 00:23:36,414
I'LL MAKE SURE SHE GETS         
THE BEST SPECIALISTS.           


301
00:23:36,482 --> 00:23:40,351
        THERE IS NO TIME.       
        SHE COULD GO INTO SEPTIC
        SHOCK OR A COMA.        


302
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:42,419
            I NEED TO GET HER   
            THE PENICILLIN.     


303
00:23:42,488 --> 00:23:44,555
        <i> THE EYE SHOULD BE HERE</i> 
        <i> IN A FEW MINUTES.</i>      


304
00:23:44,624 --> 00:23:47,724
    THAT WILL GIVE US           
    ABOUT 20 MINUTES OF CALM.   


305
00:23:47,793 --> 00:23:51,161
- HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?       
- JAROD USED TO BE A WEATHERMAN 
  IN PUERTO RICO.               


306
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:54,932
MAMA, PAPA,                     
POUVEZ-VOUS ME VOIR?            


307
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,068
        SIMONE, TOUT VA BIEN.   
        TOUT VA BIEN.           


308
00:23:58,137 --> 00:24:01,172
- WHAT'S SHE SAYING?            
- SHE'S LOOKING FOR THE SKY.    


309
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:05,509
<i>HER MOTHER TOLD HER</i>             
<i>BEFORE SHE DIED THAT SHE WOULD</i>  
<i>LOOK AFTER HER FROM THE SKY,</i>    


310
00:24:05,577 --> 00:24:08,012
    THAT THE SUN AND THE MOON   
    WOULD BE HER EYES.          


311
00:24:11,383 --> 00:24:14,351
    I'M GOING TO THE BOATHOUSE. 


312
00:24:14,420 --> 00:24:16,853
            ARE YOU GOING       
            TO LET HER DIE?     


313
00:24:18,690 --> 00:24:20,924
    SAM, CUFF HIM.              


314
00:24:25,999 --> 00:24:28,598
I'M GOING WITH YOU.             


315
00:24:31,103 --> 00:24:35,472
    PAT, TRY TO KEEP HER        
    TEMPERATURE UNDER CONTROL   
    WHILE I'M GONE.             


316
00:24:35,541 --> 00:24:38,976
        <i> I'M COUNTING ON YOU.</i>   
        <i> SO IS SHE.</i>             


317
00:24:39,045 --> 00:24:42,879
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


318
00:24:52,291 --> 00:24:54,358
YOU'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING.   


319
00:24:54,427 --> 00:24:56,627
        CALL ME MOTHER TERESA   
        FROM NOW ON.            


320
00:24:56,696 --> 00:24:59,396
    - IT DOESN'T SUIT YOU.      
    - WHAT?                     


321
00:24:59,465 --> 00:25:02,333
THIS FACADE YOU PUT UP.         


322
00:25:02,401 --> 00:25:06,337
YOU TRY TO ACT LIKE YOUR FATHER,
BUT HE'S NOT WHO YOU ARE.       


323
00:25:06,406 --> 00:25:08,505
        THIS IS BUSINESS,       
        JAROD, NOT PERSONAL.    


324
00:25:08,574 --> 00:25:11,741
    <i> NO MATTER HOW HARD YOU TRY</i> 
    <i> AND MAKE IT THAT WAY.</i>      
IT'S PERSONAL TO ME.            


325
00:25:11,810 --> 00:25:14,411
        THEN WHY CAN'T YOU LEAVE
        MY MOTHER OUT OF IT?    


326
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:17,681
BECAUSE SHE TRIED TO RESCUE ME  
FROM YOUR FATHER.               


327
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:21,585
        -<i> [ Tree Falls ]</i>        
        - [ Tires Skidding ]    


328
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:26,857
                    WHAT NOW?   


329
00:25:26,926 --> 00:25:28,992
<i>IT'S LESS THAN A MILE.</i>          


330
00:25:29,061 --> 00:25:31,595
IF WE MOVE FAST,                
WE'LL BEAT THE EYE.             


331
00:25:31,663 --> 00:25:34,765
IT SURE WOULD BE                
A LOT EASIER WITHOUT THESE.     


332
00:25:37,736 --> 00:25:40,938
        YOU TRY ANYTHING,       
        AND I'LL PUT A BULLET   
        THROUGH YOUR KNEE.      


333
00:25:41,006 --> 00:25:43,573
I THOUGHT IT WAS MY FOOT.       


334
00:26:03,996 --> 00:26:06,563
FEVER'S NOT BREAKING.           


335
00:26:06,632 --> 00:26:08,899
COME ON, KIDDO.                 


336
00:26:10,269 --> 00:26:13,003
                WORK WITH ME.   


337
00:26:15,274 --> 00:26:17,207
    WHY ARE YOU AFTER JAROD?    


338
00:26:17,276 --> 00:26:19,743
SHUT UP AND WATCH THE KID.      


339
00:26:23,549 --> 00:26:26,916
        - I NEED MORE ICE.      
        - I'LL GET IT.          


340
00:26:31,290 --> 00:26:33,423
    [ Quiet Muttering ]         


341
00:26:33,492 --> 00:26:36,627
JAROD, WHAT'S TAKING SO LONG?   


342
00:26:36,696 --> 00:26:42,432
        <i> I'VE GOT IT. THERE'S</i>   
        <i> STILL PLENTY OF TIME.</i>  
        <i> SIMONE'S GONNA BE OKAY.</i>


343
00:26:44,069 --> 00:26:46,836
            <i> HONEY, I'M HOME.</i>   


344
00:26:57,950 --> 00:27:02,186
    [ TV Announcer ]            
    CASSANDRA, CLOCKED AT SPEEDS
    UP TO 160 MILES AN HOUR--   


345
00:27:02,254 --> 00:27:04,688
        YOU HEARD FROM HER?     
    [ Continues, Indistinct ]   


346
00:27:04,757 --> 00:27:06,690
NO. I'M CONCERNED.              


347
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:09,292
            <i> SO AM I.</i>           
<i>OH, YOU ARE?</i>                    


348
00:27:09,361 --> 00:27:11,762
MR. RAINES                      
ORDERED HER INTO THAT.          


349
00:27:13,199 --> 00:27:15,432
        DO YOU HAVE A PROBLEM   
        WITH RAINES?            


350
00:27:15,501 --> 00:27:17,501
HE IS OUT OF CONTROL.           


351
00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:20,170
        <i> RAINES ISN'T. JAROD IS.</i>


352
00:27:20,238 --> 00:27:23,006
    TORMENTING MY DAUGHTER      
    WITH LIES ABOUT HER MOTHER. 


353
00:27:23,075 --> 00:27:25,309
        LIES?                   
            <i> YOU SAW HER LAST.</i>  


354
00:27:25,378 --> 00:27:28,512
        YOU KNEW HER CONDITION. 


355
00:27:28,581 --> 00:27:31,514
    HER ONLY OPTION WAS SUICIDE.


356
00:27:31,583 --> 00:27:37,220
MRS. PARKER, GOD REST HER SOUL, 
WAS MANIC-DEPRESSIVE.           


357
00:27:37,289 --> 00:27:40,724
HER MARRIAGE                    
WAS FALLING APART,              


358
00:27:40,793 --> 00:27:44,394
AND, OF COURSE, THERE WAS       
THE QUESTION OF HER BEATING.    


359
00:27:45,697 --> 00:27:48,065
        EXACTLY WHAT DID SHE SAY
        ABOUT THAT?             


360
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:50,067
I CAN'T DISCLOSE THAT.          


361
00:27:50,136 --> 00:27:52,269
BUT YOU KNOW PSYCHIATRISTS,     
MR. PARKER.                     


362
00:27:52,338 --> 00:27:54,304
WE WRITE EVERYTHING DOWN.       


363
00:27:55,607 --> 00:27:57,540
                SO DO I.        


364
00:27:57,609 --> 00:28:00,210
YOUR WIFE WAS MY PATIENT.       


365
00:28:00,278 --> 00:28:03,546
THE DETAILS OF HER SESSIONS     
ARE PRIVILEGED.                 


366
00:28:03,615 --> 00:28:06,749
    I HAVE PRIVILEGES, SYDNEY.  


367
00:28:08,387 --> 00:28:10,387
I'M WELL AWARE OF THAT.         


368
00:28:12,624 --> 00:28:15,092
[ Mr. Parker On Speaker ]       
ANYTHING ELSE, DOCTOR?          


369
00:28:15,161 --> 00:28:17,594
[ Sydney ]                      
NO.                             


370
00:28:25,737 --> 00:28:29,440
        <i> [ Jarod ]</i>              
        <i> THAT ROPE WAS TOUGHER</i>  
        <i> THAN I THOUGHT.</i>        


371
00:28:29,508 --> 00:28:32,242
        LOOKS LIKE IT COST YOU  
        A MOLAR.                


372
00:28:32,311 --> 00:28:35,612
TWO. NOW SHUT UP!               


373
00:28:35,681 --> 00:28:39,016
YOU NEVER HAD TO CLEAN UP       
ONE OF YOUR MESSES,             
HAVE YOU, JAROD?                


374
00:28:39,084 --> 00:28:42,385
<i>YOU SHOULD'VE MET THAT COP</i>      
<i> YOU FRAMED IN MIAMI.</i>           


375
00:28:42,454 --> 00:28:46,256
    - WHAT A WHINER!            
    - I TOLD YOU TO SHUT        
      YOUR PIE HOLE!            


376
00:28:46,325 --> 00:28:50,260
LISTEN... GOOBER.               
THE CENTRE WILL PAY YOU--       


377
00:28:50,329 --> 00:28:52,595
    SHUT UP! SHUT UP!           


378
00:28:53,999 --> 00:28:57,801
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN             
ABOUT THE CENTRE.               


379
00:28:57,869 --> 00:29:00,337
SOON AS THIS STORM              
IS OUTTA MY FACE,               


380
00:29:00,406 --> 00:29:03,340
WE'RE TAKIN' A LITTLE           
BOAT RIDE OUT TO THE SWAMP.     


381
00:29:03,409 --> 00:29:05,975
BUT I'M THE ONLY ONE            
COMIN' BACK.                    


382
00:29:06,045 --> 00:29:09,413
TONIGHT YOU TWO                 
SLEEP WITH THE MANATEES.        


383
00:29:11,617 --> 00:29:14,551
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


384
00:29:14,620 --> 00:29:18,122
<i>[ Simone Moaning ]</i>              


385
00:29:18,190 --> 00:29:21,157
    <i> MAMA, PAPA,</i>                
    <i> POUVEZ-VOUS ME VOIR?</i>       


386
00:29:21,226 --> 00:29:23,326
        HEY, HEY. SHH, SHH, SHH.


387
00:29:23,395 --> 00:29:26,830
        SHE-- SHE CAN'T         
        KEEP ANY FOOD DOWN.     


388
00:29:26,899 --> 00:29:29,833
LET ME MAKE HER SOME JUICE.     
THE VITAMINS WILL DO HER GOOD.  


389
00:29:51,090 --> 00:29:54,791
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


390
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:56,593
<i>HEY!</i>                            


391
00:29:57,896 --> 00:30:00,463
            YOU SCARED ME.      


392
00:30:00,532 --> 00:30:02,665
STOP WASTIN' TIME.              


393
00:30:23,890 --> 00:30:27,391
YOUR CRUSADE FOR THE LITTLE GUY 
IS BACKFIRING.                  


394
00:30:27,459 --> 00:30:29,927
HOW DOES IT FEEL                
TO FACE THE CONSEQUENCES?       


395
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:32,930
        I SPENT AN ENTIRE LIFE  
        SIMULATING REALITY.     


396
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,032
        CONSEQUENCES?           
        THEY FEEL PRETTY GOOD.  


397
00:30:41,473 --> 00:30:44,875
JAROD, WHAT DID YOU MEAN        
WHEN YOU SAID MY MOTHER         
TRIED TO SAVE YOU?              


398
00:30:44,944 --> 00:30:48,345
            SHE WAS PLANNING    
            ON SMUGGLING ME     
            OUT OF THE CENTRE.  


399
00:30:49,949 --> 00:30:52,749
YOU WERE ONE OF THE CHILDREN    
SHE TRIED TO RESCUE?            


400
00:30:52,818 --> 00:30:56,519
    <i> SHE DIED BEFORE SHE COULD</i>  
    <i> GET TO ME OR THE OTHERS.</i>   


401
00:30:56,588 --> 00:30:59,089
        OTHERS?                 


402
00:30:59,157 --> 00:31:02,226
            <i> SHE HAD A LIST</i>     
            <i> OF SEVEN CHILDREN.</i> 


403
00:31:03,929 --> 00:31:05,863
            THE UNLUCKY ONES.   


404
00:31:05,932 --> 00:31:08,865
AND WHERE DID YOU               
GET THIS LIST?                  


405
00:31:08,934 --> 00:31:14,771
    THE MEDICAL REPORT          
    WASN'T THE ONLY THING       
    IN THE SAFETY DEPOSIT BOX.  


406
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:17,107
THE MEDICAL REPORT IS REAL.     


407
00:31:18,510 --> 00:31:20,744
[ Shudders ]                    


408
00:31:20,813 --> 00:31:24,114
I REMEMBER MY PARENTS           
FIGHTING THAT NIGHT.            


409
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:28,418
<i>SHE WENT OFF THE DEEP END.</i>      


410
00:31:28,487 --> 00:31:31,088
<i>WOULDN'T EVEN WEAR</i>              
<i>HER WEDDING RING.</i>               


411
00:31:31,156 --> 00:31:34,357
    IT WAS A BAD TIME           
    FOR MY FATHER.              


412
00:31:34,426 --> 00:31:36,960
    HOW CAN YOU STILL TRUST HIM?


413
00:31:38,797 --> 00:31:42,232
I NEVER SAW HIM HIT HER.        


414
00:31:43,535 --> 00:31:45,269
<i>EVER.</i>                           


415
00:31:45,338 --> 00:31:48,038
    <i> [ Glass Shattering ]</i>       
    <i> [ Blow Landing ]</i>           


416
00:31:49,441 --> 00:31:51,308
        [ Creaking ]            


417
00:31:54,647 --> 00:31:58,315
I NEVER SAW ANYONE.             
NOT THAT I CAN REMEMBER.        


418
00:31:58,384 --> 00:32:01,251
    <i> PEOPLE REPRESS MEMORIES.</i>   


419
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:04,120
    ESPECIALLY TRAUMATIC ONES.  


420
00:32:04,189 --> 00:32:06,856
        <i> UNLESS SOMETHING</i>       
        <i> HELPS BRING THEM OUT,</i>  


421
00:32:06,925 --> 00:32:10,961
            <i> LIKE A-- A SMELL...</i>
            <i> OR A SOUND.</i>        


422
00:32:12,465 --> 00:32:16,232
            I USED TO SELL      
            POWER MEMORY TAPES  
            ON LATE-NIGHT CABLE.


423
00:32:16,301 --> 00:32:20,203
            PERHAPS             
            YOU MISSED THAT ONE.
            LET ME HELP YOU.    


424
00:32:20,272 --> 00:32:24,475
THANKS FOR THE OFFER,           
BUT I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.  


425
00:32:24,543 --> 00:32:26,577
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


426
00:32:28,046 --> 00:32:31,981
    [ Loud Groaning ]           


427
00:32:33,953 --> 00:32:35,986
    [ Groaning ]                


428
00:32:42,561 --> 00:32:45,062
        [ Raines ]              
        IF YOU WERE             
        SO WORRIED ABOUT HER,   


429
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:47,965
            YOU SHOULD HAVE GONE
            WITH HER.           


430
00:32:48,034 --> 00:32:51,701
SHE ONLY WENT                   
BECAUSE YOU INTIMIDATED HER.    


431
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:54,704
            MISS PARKER         
            IS DOING HER JOB.   


432
00:32:54,774 --> 00:32:57,908
    I'M GLAD TO SEE SOMEONE IS. 


433
00:33:00,012 --> 00:33:03,146
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?           


434
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:08,018
        TOO MANY CIGARETTES,    
        NOT ENOUGH VACATIONS.   


435
00:33:09,455 --> 00:33:14,224
WHEN YOU WERE DR. RAINES,       
YOU WERE MY COLLEAGUE.          


436
00:33:14,293 --> 00:33:18,895
I NEVER DETECTED                
THIS OBSESSION.                 


437
00:33:18,964 --> 00:33:23,567
        I DON'T HAVE TO FOLLOW  
        THE HIPPOCRATIC OATH    
        ANYMORE.                


438
00:33:24,937 --> 00:33:28,905
        MY ONLY DIRECTIVE       
        IS TO BRING JAROD BACK. 


439
00:33:30,109 --> 00:33:34,378
        FOR THAT TO HAPPEN,     
        MISS PARKER NEEDS FOCUS.


440
00:33:34,446 --> 00:33:37,548
SHE HAS A LOT OF ISSUES         
ON HER MIND.                    


441
00:33:39,452 --> 00:33:42,886
SHE'S ALWAYS BEEN               
A CURIOUS GIRL.                 


442
00:33:42,955 --> 00:33:45,722
TAKES AFTER HER MOTHER.         


443
00:33:45,791 --> 00:33:48,592
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>WEATHER SERVICE SAYS THE EYE</i>    
<i>JUST PASSED THE ISLAND.</i>         


444
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:50,927
WE COULD-- WE COULD--           
[ Clears Throat ]               


445
00:33:50,996 --> 00:33:53,497
WE COULD BE THERE               
BY MORNING.                     


446
00:33:53,565 --> 00:33:55,265
                GET A JET.      


447
00:33:57,069 --> 00:33:59,869
        <i> COME ON, BROOTS.</i>       


448
00:33:59,939 --> 00:34:03,606
    WE WOULDN'T WANT ANY HARM   
    TO COME TO MISS PARKER.     


449
00:34:12,751 --> 00:34:15,519
                    THAT'S IT.  


450
00:34:15,588 --> 00:34:18,855
            A LITTLE TANGERINE, 
             A LITTLE KEY LIME. 


451
00:34:18,924 --> 00:34:21,057
            <i> GOOD FOR THE SOUL.</i> 


452
00:34:21,126 --> 00:34:23,860
    BUT YOU'RE STILL BURNING UP.


453
00:34:23,929 --> 00:34:25,929
    COME ON, JAROD.             


454
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:31,035
        <i> WHERE ARE YOU GOING?</i>   
TO GET SOME MORE.               


455
00:34:42,381 --> 00:34:44,948
<i>LOOKING FOR THIS?</i>               


456
00:34:50,889 --> 00:34:54,824
<i>OKAY. TIME</i>                      
<i>FOR A LITTLE BOAT RIDE.</i>         


457
00:34:54,893 --> 00:34:56,559
LADIES FIRST.                   


458
00:34:56,628 --> 00:34:59,429
    [ Grunts ]                  


459
00:34:59,498 --> 00:35:02,999
        [ Groaning ]            


460
00:35:09,675 --> 00:35:12,609
        [ Grunts, Groans ]      


461
00:35:12,678 --> 00:35:15,011
        - [ Chuckles ]          
        - DROP IT!              


462
00:35:16,915 --> 00:35:19,416
    [ Laughing ]                
    THAT'S A FLARE GUN.         


463
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:23,152
IT'S GONNA REDEFINE HEARTBURN   
UNLESS YOU DROP IT.             


464
00:35:25,591 --> 00:35:29,493
                    [ Groans ]  
WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?           


465
00:35:29,562 --> 00:35:32,930
I SNUCK IT INTO THE FIRST AID   
KIT WHEN YOU WEREN'T LOOKING.   


466
00:35:32,998 --> 00:35:35,833
[ Panting ]                     
YOU WERE GONNA USE THAT ON ME.  


467
00:35:37,002 --> 00:35:38,936
                I STILL AM.     


468
00:35:46,411 --> 00:35:49,046
<i>TRY GUMMING THROUGH THIS.</i>       


469
00:35:53,052 --> 00:35:56,486
AND YOU ARE GOING               
TO HAVE TO DISLOCATE            
A LOT MORE THAN YOUR THUMB...   


470
00:35:56,555 --> 00:35:58,822
TO GET THROUGH THAT.            


471
00:35:58,891 --> 00:36:02,325
    WHY DID YOU SAVE MY LIFE?   


472
00:36:02,394 --> 00:36:06,363
BECAUSE... I STILL REMEMBER     
THE LITTLE GIRL...              


473
00:36:06,431 --> 00:36:09,832
WHO GAVE ME MY FIRST KISS.      


474
00:36:09,901 --> 00:36:12,502
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


475
00:36:25,250 --> 00:36:28,051
<i>[ Thunder Continues ]</i>           


476
00:36:30,622 --> 00:36:35,525
            <i> [ Shutter Banging ]</i>


477
00:36:42,101 --> 00:36:43,233
        [ Creaking ]            


478
00:36:47,273 --> 00:36:49,506
    <i> [ Woman Screaming ]</i>        
    <i> [ Glass Shattering ]</i>       


479
00:36:49,575 --> 00:36:51,608
    <i> [ Man ]</i>                    
    <i> I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING!</i>  


480
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:55,078
                <i> [ Woman ]</i>      
                <i> LEAVE ME ALONE!</i>


481
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,714
        [ Creaking ]            


482
00:36:57,783 --> 00:37:01,117
        - MAMA.                 
        - MAMA.                 


483
00:37:01,187 --> 00:37:05,055
    IT'S OKAY, SWEETHEART.      
    MAMA'S ALL RIGHT.           


484
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:31,814
        MR. RAINES.             


485
00:37:43,328 --> 00:37:45,295
                        HEY.    


486
00:37:45,364 --> 00:37:48,030
                - HEY!          
                - WHAT?         


487
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:52,536
        DON'T YOU PEOPLE KEEP   
        A SPARE KEY TO THAT CAGE
        AROUND HERE?            


488
00:37:52,604 --> 00:37:54,871
YES, WE DO.                     


489
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:58,141
IT'S IN THAT MIAMI HEAT         
ASHTRAY ON THE DESK.            


490
00:37:58,209 --> 00:38:00,810
TRICK IS GETTING THERE.         


491
00:38:00,879 --> 00:38:04,847
        LOOK, WE BOTH WANT      
        TO CATCH JAROD, RIGHT?  


492
00:38:04,916 --> 00:38:06,849
OH, YEAH.                       


493
00:38:06,919 --> 00:38:10,987
    <i> SO YOU JUST FLIP YOUR CAGE</i> 
    <i> OVER A FEW TIMES.</i>          


494
00:38:11,056 --> 00:38:14,724
    YOU HELP ME CATCH HIM,      
    AND YOU WON'T JUST GET PAID.


495
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:20,497
        I'LL MAKE SURE THAT     
        YOU GET A SWEET REWARD. 


496
00:38:32,711 --> 00:38:36,412
[ Grunting ]                    


497
00:38:42,288 --> 00:38:45,355
        PUT SOME MUSCLE INTO IT!


498
00:38:45,424 --> 00:38:48,591
[ Grunts ]                      
                        YES!    


499
00:38:57,602 --> 00:39:00,137
<i>[ Bird Squawking ]</i>              


500
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:06,410
                    AHH.        


501
00:39:11,149 --> 00:39:15,518
SO, WHEN DO I GET               
THAT SWEET REWARD?              


502
00:39:15,587 --> 00:39:18,121
            [ Chuckles ]        
            NOW.                


503
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:21,358
            [ Grunts ]          
[ Groans ]                      


504
00:39:29,067 --> 00:39:31,467
STORM'S CLEAR. WE'LL BE LANDING 
IN FIVE, DOCTOR.                


505
00:39:36,909 --> 00:39:40,644
    - JAROD.                    
    - WHERE'S MISS PARKER?      


506
00:39:40,712 --> 00:39:43,613
<i>I SAID, WHERE IS SHE?</i>           


507
00:39:43,682 --> 00:39:45,782
<i>SHE HAD A DATE.</i>                 


508
00:39:45,851 --> 00:39:48,284
            DROP IT AND STAND   
            AGAINST THE WALL!   


509
00:39:48,353 --> 00:39:50,754
SHE NEEDS THIS.                 


510
00:39:55,427 --> 00:39:59,128
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO, SAM?  
YOU GONNA KILL ME?              


511
00:40:00,499 --> 00:40:03,433
I DON'T THINK YOU HAVE          
THE AUTHORIZATION TO DO THAT.   


512
00:40:03,501 --> 00:40:06,569
    -<i> [ Glass Shattering ]</i>      
    - WHOA!                     


513
00:40:06,638 --> 00:40:08,438
        - [ Laughs ]            
        - THANK YOU.            


514
00:40:08,507 --> 00:40:11,241
I SHOULD'VE DONE THAT SOONER.   


515
00:40:13,011 --> 00:40:16,079
            - SIMONE.           
            - JAROD.            


516
00:40:16,147 --> 00:40:19,149
            THIS'LL HURT        
            JUST A LITTLE BIT,  


517
00:40:19,217 --> 00:40:23,587
        BUT I PROMISE YOU--     
        IT'S GONNA MAKE YOU FEEL
        A WHOLE LOT BETTER.     


518
00:40:23,655 --> 00:40:25,788
        STORM IS OVER?          


519
00:40:25,857 --> 00:40:28,124
            YES. IT'S OVER.     


520
00:40:30,228 --> 00:40:33,429
<i>[ Helicopter Approaching ]</i>      


521
00:41:10,769 --> 00:41:12,702
HELP!                           


522
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:17,807
[ Grunts ]                      
HE'S A MANIAC.                  
A MANIAC!                       


523
00:41:17,876 --> 00:41:22,712
HE TRIED TO TEACH ME A LESSON.  
HE THINKS HE'S SOME KIND        
OF ONE-MAN JUDGE AND JURY!      


524
00:41:22,781 --> 00:41:25,381
                WHERE IS HE?    
THAT WAY.                       
BY THE FRONT DESK.              


525
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:28,485
OUT. BUNGALOW 32.               
IT'S WAY, WAY, WAY TO THE BACK. 


526
00:41:38,530 --> 00:41:41,597
    OH, YEAH.                   
     OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.      


527
00:41:41,667 --> 00:41:44,267
            SUCKERS.            


528
00:41:53,645 --> 00:41:56,445
<i>[ Helicopter Rotors Whirring ]</i>  


529
00:41:56,514 --> 00:41:58,581
    READY?                      


530
00:42:01,452 --> 00:42:05,655
<i>YOUR MAMA AND PAPA--</i>            
<i>THEY CAN SEE YOU NOW.</i>           


531
00:42:29,314 --> 00:42:31,080
    [ Laughing ]                


532
00:43:08,186 --> 00:43:12,522
    I WAS CLOSE, AND I LEARNED  
    A FEW THINGS THAT ARE GOING 
    TO GET ME EVEN CLOSER.      


533
00:43:12,590 --> 00:43:14,958
    THE STATUS QUO REMAINS?     


534
00:43:15,026 --> 00:43:18,628
            WE HAVE OUR DEAL,   
            BUT IT'S NOT QUITE  
            STATUS QUO.         


535
00:43:18,697 --> 00:43:21,931
    HOW SO?                     


536
00:43:28,139 --> 00:43:30,473
        NO MORE SURVEILLANCE.   


537
00:43:30,542 --> 00:43:34,844
            NO LIE DETECTORS.   
             NO MORE GAMES.     


538
00:43:34,913 --> 00:43:37,781
                YOU SECOND-GUESS
                MY WORK AGAIN,  


539
00:43:37,849 --> 00:43:40,816
        I'LL PUT A BULLET       
        IN THAT PET OXYGEN TANK,


540
00:43:40,885 --> 00:43:43,352
AND THEY'LL HAVE TO             
CLEAN YOU UP WITH TWEEZERS.     


541
00:43:43,421 --> 00:43:46,055
        I CATCH JAROD MY WAY.   


542
00:43:46,124 --> 00:43:49,158
        AND ONCE HE'S           
        IN THE CENTRE, I'M GONE.


543
00:43:49,228 --> 00:43:53,496
            THAT'S THE DEAL.    
            ARE WE CLEAR?       


544
00:43:53,565 --> 00:43:56,566
[ Strained ]                    
AS A BELL.                      


545
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:59,469
                    [ Breathes ]


546
00:44:02,407 --> 00:44:04,841
I'LL SEE YOU LATER, DADDY.      


547
00:44:10,715 --> 00:44:13,049
        GOOD TO HAVE YOU BACK.  


548
00:44:42,180 --> 00:44:46,816
<i>[ Miss Parker Reading ]</i>         
<i>"MY DEAREST DAUGHTER, THIS RING</i> 
<i> WAS YOUR GREAT-GRANDMOTHER'S.</i>  


549
00:44:46,885 --> 00:44:49,485
<i>"IF SOMETHING SHOULD HAPPEN</i>     
<i> TO ME, I LEAVE IT FOR YOU.</i>     


550
00:44:49,554 --> 00:44:52,355
<i>MAYBE YOU'LL HAVE</i>               
<i>BETTER LUCK. MOM."</i>              


551
00:45:10,475 --> 00:45:13,042
            <i> [ Phone Ringing ]</i>  


552
00:45:16,915 --> 00:45:19,582
    - WHAT?                     
    - DID YOU GET THE RING?     


553
00:45:19,650 --> 00:45:22,318
<i>[ Miss Parker On Phone ]</i>        
<i>YES. THANK YOU, JAROD.</i>          


554
00:45:22,386 --> 00:45:24,787
    [ Jarod On Phone ]          
    DID YOU FIND YOUR ANSWER?   


555
00:45:24,856 --> 00:45:29,125
I THINK I KNOW WHO KILLED MY    
MOTHER, BUT RIGHT NOW I'M MORE  
CONCERNED WITH WHY SHE DIED.    


556
00:45:29,194 --> 00:45:31,894
IT WAS FOR THE CHILDREN.        


557
00:45:31,963 --> 00:45:34,764
        FOR YOU, JAROD.         


558
00:45:34,833 --> 00:45:40,102
    THE WAY I SEE IT,           
    SHE DIED TRYING TO SAVE YOU.


559
00:45:40,171 --> 00:45:43,305
        YOU'RE ANGRY.           
I WON'T STOP CHASING YOU.       


560
00:45:43,374 --> 00:45:45,975
    AND I WON'T CHASE           
    MY PAST ANYMORE.            


561
00:45:46,044 --> 00:45:48,444
    WHAT IF IT CHASES YOU?      


562
00:45:48,513 --> 00:45:50,613
I'LL IGNORE IT.                 


563
00:45:50,682 --> 00:45:53,949
            YOU MAKE THE RULES. 
THAT'S JUST THE WAY I LIKE IT.  


564
00:45:57,522 --> 00:46:00,089
        NICE BOOTS. SNAKESKIN?  


565
00:46:00,158 --> 00:46:02,425
    MM-MMM. GATOR.              


566
00:46:40,431 --> 00:46:41,464
            [ Mews ]            


